1
00:00:02,069 --> 00:00:03,026
- Peralta, there was
a botched B & E

2
00:00:03,070 --> 00:00:04,332
at a jewelry store on Atlantic

3
00:00:04,375 --> 00:00:06,116
that just turned into
a hostage situation.

4
00:00:06,160 --> 00:00:07,683
They want you
to be the negotiator.

5
00:00:07,726 --> 00:00:10,033
- Oh, my God, my prayers
have finally been answered.

6
00:00:10,077 --> 00:00:11,208
- You prayed
for a hostage situation?

7
00:00:11,252 --> 00:00:12,993
- Yes, I did.
Every single day.

8
00:00:13,036 --> 00:00:14,559
- I don't understand.
Why isn't ESU handling this?

9
00:00:14,603 --> 00:00:17,127
- Apparently, the hostage-taker
asked for Jake by name.

10
00:00:17,171 --> 00:00:18,955
- Oh, yes, it's getting
even cooler.

11
00:00:18,999 --> 00:00:20,565
Oh, man, I wonder who it is.
Ooh!

12
00:00:20,609 --> 00:00:22,393
Maybe it's the brother
of someone I put away for life.

13
00:00:22,437 --> 00:00:24,613
Ooh! Or the identical twin of
someone I put away for life.

14
00:00:24,656 --> 00:00:26,354
Ooh! Or the fraternal twin of—
- Jake!

15
00:00:26,397 --> 00:00:27,703
Just get down there!
Take Diaz with you.

16
00:00:27,746 --> 00:00:29,270
- Yep. Yep, yep, yep.
How do I look?

17
00:00:29,313 --> 00:00:31,141
It doesn't matter.
Let's go negotiate!

18
00:00:33,404 --> 00:00:35,406
Hey, everyone, I'm here.

19
00:00:35,450 --> 00:00:37,582
I'm Jake Peralta,
the negotiator.

20
00:00:37,626 --> 00:00:40,063
- The negotiator, yes.

21
00:00:40,107 --> 00:00:42,283
Who are you?
- Dennis Kole, ESU.

22
00:00:42,326 --> 00:00:44,546
This was my crime scene
before you bozos got here.

23
00:00:44,589 --> 00:00:46,069
- Nice to meet you too, Dennis.

24
00:00:46,113 --> 00:00:48,071
- I've spent ten years
as a negotiator

25
00:00:48,115 --> 00:00:50,421
and you just took
my first hostage situation.

26
00:00:50,465 --> 00:00:52,946
All I've done up till now is
talk jumpers off of rooftops.

27
00:00:52,989 --> 00:00:55,209
- But that must be satisfying
in its own way, right?

28
00:00:55,252 --> 00:00:58,386
- Yeah, really satisfying
saving a crazy person's life.

29
00:00:58,429 --> 00:00:59,996
Whatever.
Here's a little advice.

30
00:01:00,040 --> 00:01:01,998
I don't like you two.
- Not so much advice

31
00:01:02,042 --> 00:01:04,392
as it is a hurtful statement
based on limited interaction.

32
00:01:04,435 --> 00:01:06,698
- He wants to talk to you.

33
00:01:06,742 --> 00:01:08,048
Get the hell in there.

34
00:01:08,091 --> 00:01:10,615
- Ooh, it says
"negotiator" on it.

35
00:01:12,661 --> 00:01:15,098
This is Jake Peralta.

36
00:01:15,142 --> 00:01:17,144
I am unarmed

37
00:01:17,187 --> 00:01:19,624
and I'm approaching
the building

38
00:01:19,668 --> 00:01:26,718
♪

39
00:01:28,720 --> 00:01:32,028
You wanted to talk to me?
- Keep those hands in the air.

40
00:01:32,072 --> 00:01:33,769
And wave 'em like
you just don't care.

41
00:01:35,249 --> 00:01:36,641
- I'm just messing with you,
Peralta.

42
00:01:36,685 --> 00:01:38,339
Put your hands down,
give me a hug, baby.

43
00:01:38,382 --> 00:01:39,514
- Judy!

44
00:01:42,560 --> 00:01:49,654
♪

45
00:01:59,534 --> 00:02:01,231
- Sergeant,
a member of

46
00:02:01,275 --> 00:02:03,059
the Commissioner selection
committee is coming in today

47
00:02:03,103 --> 00:02:04,495
to tour the precinct
and do some interviews.

48
00:02:04,539 --> 00:02:05,801
Would you mind
speaking with her?

49
00:02:05,844 --> 00:02:07,498
- Of course.
Terry loves answering

50
00:02:07,542 --> 00:02:08,673
the hard questions.

51
00:02:08,717 --> 00:02:10,153
- Oh, here she is.

52
00:02:10,197 --> 00:02:11,154
I guess you don't have
time to take off

53
00:02:11,198 --> 00:02:12,373
those ridiculous suspenders.

54
00:02:12,416 --> 00:02:14,114
- Hello, Miss Sumter.

55
00:02:14,157 --> 00:02:15,463
- Hello, Captain.

56
00:02:15,506 --> 00:02:17,030
I'm excited to speak
to you subordinates

57
00:02:17,073 --> 00:02:18,509
and learn more about
your management style.

58
00:02:18,553 --> 00:02:20,642
- I thought you could talk
to Sergeant Jeffords here.

59
00:02:20,685 --> 00:02:22,470
Oh, um...

60
00:02:22,513 --> 00:02:24,298
I'd rather not talk
to a supervisor.

61
00:02:24,341 --> 00:02:26,300
I was hoping to interview
one of your detectives.

62
00:02:26,343 --> 00:02:28,519
Perhaps, um... him?

63
00:02:28,563 --> 00:02:30,130
- No!

64
00:02:30,173 --> 00:02:33,437
- There was a wasp near me,

65
00:02:33,481 --> 00:02:35,135
which has since disappeared.

66
00:02:35,178 --> 00:02:37,180
You can interview
Detective Hitchcock

67
00:02:37,224 --> 00:02:40,227
and I am completely fine
with that.

68
00:02:41,402 --> 00:02:42,620
- I gotta admit, man.

69
00:02:42,664 --> 00:02:44,492
I thought you'd be happy
to see me.

70
00:02:44,535 --> 00:02:46,189
Why you being so weird.
- Oh, I don't know.

71
00:02:46,233 --> 00:02:47,321
I didn't sleep well last night,

72
00:02:47,364 --> 00:02:48,626
so I'm probably tired
from that.

73
00:02:48,670 --> 00:02:50,367
Oh, and also,
this is a hostage situation!

74
00:02:50,411 --> 00:02:53,370
- Wow!
It's like that.

75
00:02:53,414 --> 00:02:55,111
- Yes, it's like that.
What the hell?

76
00:02:55,155 --> 00:02:56,634
I thought you went straight?
- I did.

77
00:02:56,678 --> 00:02:58,375
I'm a high-end car broker now.

78
00:02:58,419 --> 00:03:00,334
I procure luxury vehicles
for the rich and famous

79
00:03:00,377 --> 00:03:01,639
and I do it legally.

80
00:03:01,683 --> 00:03:03,293
Last week I dropped off
a Bugatti

81
00:03:03,337 --> 00:03:04,599
to the kid with the lisp
from "Stranger Things."

82
00:03:04,642 --> 00:03:06,470
Was he cool?

83
00:03:06,514 --> 00:03:08,124
Do him and the rest of the gang
hang out in real life?

84
00:03:08,168 --> 00:03:09,473
You know what? No.
We are not chatting right now.

85
00:03:09,517 --> 00:03:10,735
You have three hostages.

86
00:03:10,779 --> 00:03:12,346
- You mean Pam
and the two Bobs?

87
00:03:12,389 --> 00:03:14,087
They not hostages.
I prefer to call them

88
00:03:14,130 --> 00:03:15,610
"collateral friendships."

89
00:03:15,653 --> 00:03:17,481
I gave 'em each 500 bucks
out of my own pocket.

90
00:03:17,525 --> 00:03:19,570
- Thanks again, Doug.
- You the man, Doug.

91
00:03:19,614 --> 00:03:21,659
- Actually, I'd rather
still not be a hostage.

92
00:03:21,703 --> 00:03:23,183
- Pam hasn't come around
on me yet.

93
00:03:23,226 --> 00:03:25,098
Tell her I'm a nice person,
Jake.

94
00:03:25,141 --> 00:03:26,621
- I'm sorry. Officer, are you
friends with this criminal?

95
00:03:26,664 --> 00:03:28,449
- No, not really.
- Absolutely, best friends.

96
00:03:28,492 --> 00:03:30,146
- It's a layered relationship,
Pam.

97
00:03:30,190 --> 00:03:32,105
- Best friends.
- Judy, get over here.

98
00:03:33,497 --> 00:03:35,543
What is going on, man?
- This isn't my fault.

99
00:03:35,586 --> 00:03:36,892
Two years ago
before I went straight,

100
00:03:36,935 --> 00:03:38,546
I stole a car
from a drug dealer.

101
00:03:38,589 --> 00:03:41,157
Martin Halloway.
- Oh, no, Judy, he's a bad guy.

102
00:03:41,201 --> 00:03:42,637
- I know.
When I realized it was his car,

103
00:03:42,680 --> 00:03:44,421
I torched it along
with the drugs

104
00:03:44,465 --> 00:03:45,857
that were in the trunk
that I didn't know about.

105
00:03:45,901 --> 00:03:47,511
- Oh, no, Judy.
Trunk drugs?

106
00:03:47,555 --> 00:03:48,817
- Millions of dollars of them.

107
00:03:48,860 --> 00:03:50,601
Halloway just found out
it was me.

108
00:03:50,645 --> 00:03:52,603
Said I had to do a job for him
to pay off my debt.

109
00:03:52,647 --> 00:03:53,909
- But did you tell him
you went straight?

110
00:03:53,952 --> 00:03:55,519
Did you tell him about Dustin?
- I did.

111
00:03:55,563 --> 00:03:57,304
He said he doesn't watch
"Stranger Things."

112
00:03:57,347 --> 00:03:59,306
- Oh, this guy is the worst.
- I know.

113
00:03:59,349 --> 00:04:01,264
He said he's gonna kill my mom
if I don't do this job.

114
00:04:01,308 --> 00:04:02,570
- He can't do that.
I love your mom.

115
00:04:02,613 --> 00:04:04,441
- So do I.
That's why I'm here

116
00:04:04,485 --> 00:04:06,356
stealing this big ole bag
of diamonds.

117
00:04:06,400 --> 00:04:08,402
Jake, you know how dangerous
this dude can be.

118
00:04:08,445 --> 00:04:11,144
I need you to help me
save my mama.

119
00:04:11,187 --> 00:04:12,493
- Easy.

120
00:04:12,536 --> 00:04:13,842
I got a plan that's
good for everyone.

121
00:04:13,885 --> 00:04:15,626
All I need is for you to...

122
00:04:15,670 --> 00:04:17,802
- Let him go so he can
arrange a drop with Halloway.

123
00:04:17,846 --> 00:04:19,674
We arrest Halloway,
save Judy's mom,

124
00:04:19,717 --> 00:04:22,546
and Judy turns himself in,
and why is that amazing, Rosa?

125
00:04:22,590 --> 00:04:24,461
- Halloway's a huge crime boss.

126
00:04:24,505 --> 00:04:25,810
- NYPD's been trying
to get Halloway for years.

127
00:04:25,854 --> 00:04:27,334
- That's it.

128
00:04:27,377 --> 00:04:28,639
- Yeah, it is.
So, since we all agree,

129
00:04:28,683 --> 00:04:30,293
I'll go tell Judy
that the plan is on.

130
00:04:30,337 --> 00:04:32,469
- We don't all agree.
He's trapped and desperate.

131
00:04:32,513 --> 00:04:34,297
Everything he told you
is a lie.

132
00:04:34,341 --> 00:04:36,691
- That's all negotiating is.

133
00:04:36,734 --> 00:04:38,649
Two liars lying to each other

134
00:04:38,693 --> 00:04:40,738
until one liar stands
too close to the window

135
00:04:40,782 --> 00:04:42,262
and gets shot in the head.

136
00:04:42,305 --> 00:04:44,177
- That can't be
all negotiating is.

137
00:04:44,220 --> 00:04:45,613
- It absolutely is.
Now, get in there

138
00:04:45,656 --> 00:04:47,658
and coax him to a window.
Snipers to one.

139
00:04:47,702 --> 00:04:49,312
The window plan is on.
I repeat.

140
00:04:49,356 --> 00:04:50,835
The window plan is on.
- No, no, no, no, no!

141
00:04:50,879 --> 00:04:52,794
Snipers to zero.
Snipers take a nap.

142
00:04:52,837 --> 00:04:54,796
The nap plan is on.
It's nap time, snipers.

143
00:04:56,406 --> 00:04:58,408
- Amy, Gina, you came!

144
00:04:58,452 --> 00:05:00,323
- You think I'd miss
opening day of your food truck?

145
00:05:00,367 --> 00:05:02,673
I'm your biggest fan.
- Also your biggest investor.

146
00:05:02,717 --> 00:05:04,806
She was freaking out she was
gonna lose a ton of money.

147
00:05:04,849 --> 00:05:06,329
- I told you that
in confidence.

148
00:05:06,373 --> 00:05:07,852
- We don't have that kind
of relationship.

149
00:05:07,896 --> 00:05:09,985
- Well, don't worry.
I'm feeling good.

150
00:05:10,028 --> 00:05:11,769
"The One Thing" truck
is ready to serve.

151
00:05:11,813 --> 00:05:12,857
- Yeah.

152
00:05:12,901 --> 00:05:14,337
We only serve one thing:

153
00:05:14,381 --> 00:05:16,339
the perfect meatball sandwich—

154
00:05:16,383 --> 00:05:18,472
made exactly the way
Nana Boyle used to.

155
00:05:18,515 --> 00:05:20,343
I can't believe this
is finally happening.

156
00:05:22,780 --> 00:05:24,956
Ahh!

157
00:05:25,000 --> 00:05:27,002
- Sorry, I'm a bit stressed.
Jason and Jeff,

158
00:05:27,045 --> 00:05:28,525
the guys I hired
to work the truck,

159
00:05:28,569 --> 00:05:30,397
called in sick
so I'm all alone.

160
00:05:30,440 --> 00:05:31,876
What a fun opportunity.

161
00:05:31,920 --> 00:05:33,835
- Okay, Boyle,
stop freaking out.

162
00:05:33,878 --> 00:05:35,706
I have the day off.
I can step in and help.

163
00:05:35,750 --> 00:05:37,273
- Yeah, me too.
I'm not off,

164
00:05:37,317 --> 00:05:38,709
but I come and go
as I please.

165
00:05:38,753 --> 00:05:41,234
It's part of my charm.
I'm like an outdoor cat.

166
00:05:42,539 --> 00:05:44,715
- ESU won't take your deal.
They think you're lying.

167
00:05:44,759 --> 00:05:46,891
- I'm not lying.
I don't wanna be a criminal.

168
00:05:46,935 --> 00:05:48,763
I love my life
as a average citizen.

169
00:05:48,806 --> 00:05:50,721
I voted for the first time
this year.

170
00:05:50,765 --> 00:05:51,896
Ed Breakfast for school board.

171
00:05:51,940 --> 00:05:53,376
- I don't know.

172
00:05:53,420 --> 00:05:54,551
He had a funny name.
He deserves a shot.

173
00:05:54,595 --> 00:05:56,336
- That's why I voted
for Stacy Ladle.

174
00:05:56,379 --> 00:05:58,033
Anyway, I'm sorry, but
they're not cutting a deal.

175
00:05:58,076 --> 00:05:59,730
I gotta turn myself in

176
00:05:59,774 --> 00:06:02,559
and let Halloway kill my mama?
- Actually...

177
00:06:02,603 --> 00:06:04,735
there might another way
to get this done.

178
00:06:04,779 --> 00:06:06,694
- I've taken
your negotiator hostage.

179
00:06:06,737 --> 00:06:08,913
If you come in here,
I will shoot him.

180
00:06:08,957 --> 00:06:12,569
- Just do whatever he says!
My life is in his hands!

181
00:06:14,310 --> 00:06:16,443
That was so much fun!

182
00:06:16,486 --> 00:06:18,401
- Oh, man, you sounded
really scary.

183
00:06:18,445 --> 00:06:19,663
- No, no, it was all you.

184
00:06:19,707 --> 00:06:21,404
The tremble in your voice
sold it.

185
00:06:21,448 --> 00:06:23,493
"Just do whatever he wants."
- I just made that up.

186
00:06:23,537 --> 00:06:25,626
Ah, I was so in the moment.

187
00:06:25,669 --> 00:06:28,455
You are a great hostage.
- Oh, thanks, Judy.

188
00:06:28,498 --> 00:06:30,544
You're a great hostage taker.
Whoop.

189
00:06:33,938 --> 00:06:35,810
both: Yes, sir.

190
00:06:39,379 --> 00:06:41,859
- I can't believe Peralta
got taken hostage.

191
00:06:41,903 --> 00:06:44,601
The good news is...

192
00:06:44,645 --> 00:06:45,907
I'm the negotiator now.

193
00:06:45,950 --> 00:06:47,343
Finally.
- Congratulations.

194
00:06:47,387 --> 00:06:49,693
- I've been waiting
for this moment for so long,

195
00:06:49,737 --> 00:06:51,086
and—
- I'm ready to negotiate.

196
00:06:51,129 --> 00:06:53,654
But I'll only talk
to Rosa Diaz.

197
00:06:53,697 --> 00:06:56,091
- That's me, Dennis.
- Oh, come on!

198
00:06:56,831 --> 00:06:59,268
- Okay, I think we're ready
for a practice sandwich.

199
00:06:59,312 --> 00:07:01,183
- Sounds good, boss.
- Please call me "chef."

200
00:07:01,226 --> 00:07:03,838
That's funny.

201
00:07:03,881 --> 00:07:05,970
Chef.
- Thank you.

202
00:07:06,014 --> 00:07:09,278
- Okay, see.
The cut is a little slopey.

203
00:07:09,322 --> 00:07:11,149
I want you to cut it
straight across.

204
00:07:11,193 --> 00:07:13,108
No big deal.
Again.

205
00:07:13,151 --> 00:07:14,762
- Oh.

206
00:07:14,805 --> 00:07:15,937
Uhp, slopey.

207
00:07:15,980 --> 00:07:18,113
Don't over think it.
Again.

208
00:07:19,375 --> 00:07:20,942
Now you're not thinking enough.

209
00:07:20,985 --> 00:07:22,857
Again.

210
00:07:22,900 --> 00:07:24,380
Still slopey.
Again.

211
00:07:24,424 --> 00:07:25,903
Again!

212
00:07:25,947 --> 00:07:27,078
You know what?
Why don't we try this:

213
00:07:27,122 --> 00:07:28,341
Why don't you just
take that knife,

214
00:07:28,384 --> 00:07:29,864
put it to my throat,
and finish the job!

215
00:07:32,823 --> 00:07:34,390
- No, not at all.
- Then why are you trying

216
00:07:34,434 --> 00:07:36,392
to screw me?
- Oh, my God, Charles,

217
00:07:36,436 --> 00:07:38,829
what is going on with you?
- It's chef.

218
00:07:38,873 --> 00:07:40,396
You're not ready for this.
Gina, you're up.

219
00:07:40,440 --> 00:07:41,963
- Okay, but I'm not
calling you chef,

220
00:07:42,006 --> 00:07:44,226
and you're not yelling at me.
- Mm-hmm.

221
00:07:45,836 --> 00:07:47,272
- There you go.
- Ah, thank you.

222
00:07:47,316 --> 00:07:49,971
No slope!
A nice, straight cut!

223
00:07:50,014 --> 00:07:51,320
- Thank you.
I felt good 'cause the knife—

224
00:07:51,364 --> 00:07:52,930
- But you smushed the bread!

225
00:07:52,974 --> 00:07:55,716
It's too smushy!

226
00:07:55,759 --> 00:07:56,804
Again.

227
00:08:00,285 --> 00:08:03,201
- ♪ Rosa, Rosa, Rosa

228
00:08:03,245 --> 00:08:05,029
♪ Are you finally single?

229
00:08:05,073 --> 00:08:06,944
- No.
- ♪ I respect that

230
00:08:06,988 --> 00:08:08,772
Now come on in.
We gotta talk business.

231
00:08:08,816 --> 00:08:11,122
It's so good to see you.
Bring it in.

232
00:08:12,297 --> 00:08:13,821
- Doug Judy,
you're under arrest.

233
00:08:13,864 --> 00:08:15,692
- Wait, Rosa, stop.

234
00:08:15,736 --> 00:08:17,433
- All right, look, this is not
really a hostage situation.

235
00:08:17,477 --> 00:08:19,087
I mean, Pam and the two Bobs
are definitely being held

236
00:08:19,130 --> 00:08:20,654
against their will,
but not for much longer.

237
00:08:20,697 --> 00:08:22,133
- Jake is helping me
take down Halloway.

238
00:08:22,177 --> 00:08:24,179
We can't do it without you.

239
00:08:24,222 --> 00:08:26,355
This is like that story my dad
told me as a little kid.

240
00:08:26,399 --> 00:08:27,965
You're the frog
and he's a scorpion.

241
00:08:28,009 --> 00:08:29,314
You're gonna help him
across the river.

242
00:08:29,358 --> 00:08:31,012
And in the end,
he'll sting you,

243
00:08:31,055 --> 00:08:33,449
and then you'll both drown.
- Wow, that's dark.

244
00:08:33,493 --> 00:08:35,146
My parents didn't read
to me at all.

245
00:08:35,190 --> 00:08:36,452
