00:17:10,052 --> 00:17:11,358
He did pick up.
In your—

493
00:17:11,401 --> 00:17:13,273
- This is good-bye forever.
- No!

494
00:17:13,316 --> 00:17:15,579
Ugh, I can't believe
you deceived me.

495
00:17:15,623 --> 00:17:17,190
I can't believe you used my
love for your mother

496
00:17:17,233 --> 00:17:18,974
against me.
- I love that you love her.

497
00:17:19,018 --> 00:17:20,497
- Of course I do.
She's a living saint.

498
00:17:20,541 --> 00:17:22,499
- Amen.
Look, I wasn't lying though.

499
00:17:22,543 --> 00:17:24,414
Halloway was gonna hurt her
and you saved her life,

500
00:17:24,458 --> 00:17:26,373
but then I was all alone
with the diamonds,

501
00:17:26,416 --> 00:17:28,244
next thing I know, I'm hot
wiring a car and driving away.

502
00:17:28,288 --> 00:17:30,507
- Oh, but I thought you liked
being a good citizen?

503
00:17:30,551 --> 00:17:32,205
You voted Ed Breakfast
for school board.

504
00:17:32,248 --> 00:17:34,468
- And he immediately had
a sex scandal.

505
00:17:34,511 --> 00:17:36,209
It was very disillusioning.
- For sure.

506
00:17:36,252 --> 00:17:38,559
Our democracy is crumbling.
But what about your job?

507
00:17:38,602 --> 00:17:40,213
What about Dustin
from "Stranger Things"?

508
00:17:40,256 --> 00:17:41,562
- Famous kids are monsters.

509
00:17:41,605 --> 00:17:43,216
You do not wanna meet
Young Sheldon.

510
00:17:43,259 --> 00:17:44,565
Ah, that's disappointing.

511
00:17:44,608 --> 00:17:46,349
He was so good
in "Big Little Lies."

512
00:17:46,393 --> 00:17:47,568
Wait, no, we are not
talking about this right now!

513
00:17:47,611 --> 00:17:49,135
They could take my badge, Judy!

514
00:17:49,178 --> 00:17:51,615
- I guess Rosa was right.
I'm scorpion.

515
00:17:51,659 --> 00:17:53,313
Scorpion's gonna scorp.

516
00:17:53,356 --> 00:17:55,097
I'm sorry I can't be the man
you want me to be.

517
00:17:55,141 --> 00:17:57,012
- Damn it,
stop being so romantic.

518
00:17:57,056 --> 00:17:59,232
Now turn around
and come back to me, you fool?

519
00:17:59,275 --> 00:18:01,060
Hello?
Hello?

520
00:18:01,103 --> 00:18:02,409
He's gone.

521
00:18:02,452 --> 00:18:04,585
He broke my heart.

522
00:18:04,628 --> 00:18:07,022
Now's the time where you tell
me everything's gonna be okay.

523
00:18:07,066 --> 00:18:09,720
- Everything's gonna be okay.
- You don't know that, Rosa!

524
00:18:09,764 --> 00:18:12,506
- Ah, Hitchcock, I just got off
the phone with Anne Sumter.

525
00:18:12,549 --> 00:18:14,421
She said you really helped
my candidacy.

526
00:18:14,464 --> 00:18:16,945
- Oh, it's my pleasure, sir.
- You were so professional.

527
00:18:16,989 --> 00:18:19,165
- I know.
I didn't even fart once.

528
00:18:19,208 --> 00:18:20,601
You're right.
I can hold it.

529
00:18:20,644 --> 00:18:22,690
- You know, if you can
change for an interview,

530
00:18:22,733 --> 00:18:25,301
you can change for good.
- Nah, too much work.

531
00:18:25,345 --> 00:18:27,564
- But that's not
how "My Fair Lady" ends.

532
00:18:27,608 --> 00:18:30,306
Eliza Doolittle doesn't go back
to her old life.

533
00:18:30,350 --> 00:18:32,091
She falls in love
with Henry Higgins.

534
00:18:32,134 --> 00:18:34,049
- Well, "My Bare Lady,"
is a little different.

535
00:18:34,093 --> 00:18:36,095
It's not Eliza Doolittle
and Henry Higgins.

536
00:18:36,138 --> 00:18:38,619
It's Eliza DooEverybody
and Leroy Pipe.

537
00:18:38,662 --> 00:18:40,142
And in the end, they rub—

538
00:18:40,186 --> 00:18:42,014
- Nope.
We don't need a recap.

539
00:18:42,057 --> 00:18:44,146
Thank you for your help today.
- Anytime, Captain.

540
00:18:46,148 --> 00:18:47,758
- Hey, guys.
Uh, can we talk?

541
00:18:47,802 --> 00:18:49,499
- Let me guess,
you got overwhelmed

542
00:18:49,543 --> 00:18:51,284
and had to use
our six-sandwich technique.

543
00:18:51,327 --> 00:18:53,286
- No, my one at a time system
worked perfectly.

544
00:18:53,329 --> 00:18:54,635
- Oh.
- It's just,

545
00:18:54,678 --> 00:18:56,506
making Nana Boyle's
meatball recipe

546
00:18:56,550 --> 00:18:58,595
got me thinking
a lot about her—

547
00:18:58,639 --> 00:19:01,076
- And let me guess,
you realized she'd be ashamed

548
00:19:01,120 --> 00:19:03,296
of how you acted?
- No, Nana Boyle was a monster.

549
00:19:03,339 --> 00:19:05,080
she once yelled at me so loud,
I fainted.

550
00:19:05,124 --> 00:19:06,473
She was a hateful witch.

551
00:19:06,516 --> 00:19:07,996
She died with no friends.
- And let me guess,

552
00:19:08,040 --> 00:19:09,606
you realized
you were acting just like her

553
00:19:09,650 --> 00:19:11,304
and you felt terrible.

554
00:19:11,347 --> 00:19:12,348
- Yes.

555
00:19:12,392 --> 00:19:14,176
You don't do "and let me guess"

556
00:19:14,220 --> 00:19:15,612
until you're sure you're right.

557
00:19:15,656 --> 00:19:17,484
Can you guys forgive me?
Please?

558
00:19:17,527 --> 00:19:19,094
- Of course, Charles.

559
00:19:19,138 --> 00:19:20,574
But we will never
work for you again.

560
00:19:20,617 --> 00:19:23,011
- Yeah, that's a smart move.
It's like Jekyll and Hyde.

561
00:19:23,055 --> 00:19:24,665
I can't control
when Nana comes out.

562
00:19:24,708 --> 00:19:26,101
- Just got off the phone
with the brass.

563
00:19:26,145 --> 00:19:27,450
It doesn't look good.

564
00:19:27,494 --> 00:19:29,017
They're still trying to decide
on a punishment

565
00:19:29,061 --> 00:19:30,236
for your actions.
- Well, did you tell them

566
00:19:30,279 --> 00:19:31,498
I feel so bad
I have a tummy ache?

567
00:19:31,541 --> 00:19:33,108
- I did.
They were unaffected.

568
00:19:33,152 --> 00:19:34,588
They said they could have
justified your tactics

569
00:19:34,631 --> 00:19:36,633
if you'd come away
with Halloway and the diamonds,

570
00:19:36,677 --> 00:19:38,592
but as things stand,
there are no diamonds.

571
00:19:38,635 --> 00:19:40,202
- Well, there are
some diamonds.

572
00:19:40,246 --> 00:19:42,030
You know, the tops
of engagement rings,

573
00:19:42,074 --> 00:19:43,684
diamond mines, but, yes,
I see what you're saying

574
00:19:43,727 --> 00:19:46,121
in regards to these diamonds
and it ruining my career.

575
00:19:46,165 --> 00:19:47,688
- You're looking at
a suspension, maybe worse.

576
00:19:47,731 --> 00:19:49,516
Unless you can
track down Doug Judy

577
00:19:49,559 --> 00:19:51,692
and recover those diamonds.

578
00:19:51,735 --> 00:19:53,694
I usually run into him
about once a year.

579
00:19:53,737 --> 00:19:56,523
Wait a minute.
What have we here?

580
00:19:57,263 --> 00:20:00,570
- I've got this coupon
for a private room.

581
00:20:00,614 --> 00:20:03,095
- Yes.
Right this way.

582
00:20:03,834 --> 00:20:06,750
We already have a song
cued up for you.

583
00:20:06,794 --> 00:20:09,101
Judy.

584
00:20:09,144 --> 00:20:11,799
Thank you so much for coming.

585
00:20:11,842 --> 00:20:15,411
Look, I thought about it
and I did you dirty.

586
00:20:15,455 --> 00:20:17,152
I never meant
to cause you any trouble.

587
00:20:17,196 --> 00:20:18,545
- Yeah, well,
you caused me a lot.

588
00:20:18,588 --> 00:20:20,242
- You're talking
to a pre-recorded video,

589
00:20:20,286 --> 00:20:22,201
but it's cool.
I know what you're saying.

590
00:20:22,244 --> 00:20:24,377
I hear you in my heart.
What am I doing here?

591
00:20:24,420 --> 00:20:26,770
- I feel the same way.
You my best friend too.

592
00:20:26,814 --> 00:20:28,555
Look, I'm not coming back.

593
00:20:28,598 --> 00:20:30,165
I started a new life
here in San Diego.

594
00:20:30,209 --> 00:20:31,732
- Stupid telling me
where you are.

595
00:20:31,775 --> 00:20:33,647
- Come on, man,
I ain't in no damn San Diego.

596
00:20:33,690 --> 00:20:35,562
Everybody knows
that place sucks!

597
00:20:35,605 --> 00:20:37,259
Here's what I wanna say,
though:

598
00:20:37,303 --> 00:20:39,174
I'm sorry
I won't be at your wedding.

599
00:20:39,218 --> 00:20:43,744
But I did record you a CD
of original smush jams

600
00:20:43,787 --> 00:20:45,702
that will consummate
the marriage.

601
00:20:45,746 --> 00:20:47,400
It's on the table next to you

602
00:20:47,443 --> 00:20:49,489
along with
a little something else.

603
00:20:52,187 --> 00:20:53,754
- A French grey Le Creuset pot.

604
00:20:53,797 --> 00:20:56,235
- Now look inside it.

605
00:20:56,278 --> 00:20:58,237
The diamonds.

606
00:20:58,280 --> 00:21:00,630
Yes!
I cannot believe you actually

607
00:21:00,674 --> 00:21:03,242
brought them back—

608
00:21:03,285 --> 00:21:05,418
- Yeah, mistimed that one.
- No, you're the best.

609
00:21:05,461 --> 00:21:07,550
Look, even though
I am a scorpion,

610
00:21:07,594 --> 00:21:10,771
I will never drown
your adorable little frog ass.

611
00:21:10,814 --> 00:21:12,555
So that's what I had to say.

612
00:21:12,599 --> 00:21:15,297
I'm sure I'll see you again
at some point.

613
00:21:15,341 --> 00:21:16,864
Now that coupon you got there,

614
00:21:16,907 --> 00:21:19,432
that's for a full hour
in a private room.

615
00:21:19,475 --> 00:21:22,696
so...
- So...

616
00:21:22,739 --> 00:21:23,784
both: ♪ I said hey

617
00:21:23,827 --> 00:21:25,220
♪

618
00:21:25,264 --> 00:21:28,180
♪ What's going on?

619
00:21:28,223 --> 00:21:30,269
- Not a doctor.
Shh.

